Taking to Instagram, the rapper revealed that his father was retiring from teaching after serving the industry for 27 years.He explained that growing up, he never understood why his father had a Nissan, while the people he taught went on to own Range Rovers, until it hit him that "some people are meant to make millionaires and not millions"."In 17 days my dad is retiring from teaching after a 27 year long career. I would always ask him as a kid why he wasn't as successful as his students when they would greet him with so much enthusiasm while they drove in their Range Rovers and we were in his Nissan," he wrote."I didn't understand that some people are meant to make millionaires and not millions and their greatness is in exactly that."Cassper pointed out that he is one of his dad's most successful students."One of his most successful students went on to make history and filled up the dome last year besides many other accolades."Concluding his post, Cassper expressed his unsurpassed love for his dad, adding that he is the "greatest man" he has ever met."Today I want to say Dad, you may not have been the richest or the strongest man in the world but your overall the greatest Man I've ever met in my Life. I admire you and I love you very very much. Congrats on a great career and may the good Lord bless you with a restful retirement." Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.